1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - This is the most likely category as the paper deals with proving the correctness of cryptographic protocols for secrecy. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses families of functions used to measure the security level of atomic messages, which is related to information theory. 
3. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper may involve analyzing the efficiency of the functions used, which is related to computational complexity. 
4. cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) - The paper may involve logical reasoning and analysis of the protocol, which is related to logic in computer science. 
5. cs.PL (Programming Languages) - The paper may involve implementing the protocol and functions in a programming language, which is related to programming languages.
